body:
unhelpful error: 

```console
error[E0275]: overflow evaluating the requirement `<Fraction<_, _> as std::ops::Mul>::Output`
  |
  = note: required because of the requirements on the impl of `std::ops::Mul` for `Fraction<_, _>`
```
Code: ([playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=f1d68ea6c619238f697091f0f11e51f0))

<details><summary>Code (spoiler)</summary>
<p>

```rust
use core::{
    marker::PhantomData,
    ops::{Mul, Div},
};

pub struct Fraction<Numerator, Denominator>(PhantomData<(Numerator, Denominator)>);

trait FromUInt {
    fn from_uint<T>() -> Self;
}

impl<N, D, U> Mul<U> for Fraction<N, D>
where
    // N: Unsigned,
    // D: Unsigned + NonZero,
    U: FromUInt + Mul<Output = U> + Div<Output = U>,
{
    type Output = U;

    #[inline]
    fn mul(self, u: U) -> Self::Output {
        u * U::from_uint::<N>() / U::from_uint::<D>()
    }
}

impl<N, D, A, B> Mul<Fraction<A, B>> for Fraction<N, D>
where
    N: Mul<A>,
    D: Mul<B>,
{
    type Output = Fraction<
        <N as Mul<A>>::Output,
        <D as Mul<B>>::Output,
    >;

    #[inline]
    fn mul(self, _rhs: Fraction<A, B>) -> Self::Output {
        Self::Output::new()
    }
}
```

</p>
</details>

I've found this error while I was writing some complicated code using `typenum` so code is also complicated. Not sure how to make MRE simpler at the moment.

